oviding traversal-resistant file operations.\\n\\n**Constructor:**\\n```go\\nfunc os.OpenRoot(string) (*Root, error)\\n\\nroot, err := os.OpenRoot(\\\"/some/root/directory\\\")\\nif err != nil {\\n  return err\\n}\\ndefer root.Close()\\n```\\n\\n**Methods:**\\n```go\\nfunc (*Root) Create(string) (*File, error)\\nfunc (*Root) Lstat(string) (fs.FileInfo, error)\\nfunc (*Root) Mkdir(string, fs.FileMode) error\\nfunc (*Root) Open(string) (*File, error)\\nfunc (*Root) OpenFile(string, int, fs.FileMode) (*File, error)\\nfunc (*Root) OpenRoot(string) (*Root, error)\\nfunc (*Root) Remove(string) error\\nfunc (*Root) Stat(string) (fs.FileInfo, error)\\n```\\n\\n**Usage:**\\n```go\\nf, err := root.Open(\\\"path/to/file\\\")\\n```\\n\\n### `os.OpenInRoot` Function\\nConvenience function for opening untrusted filenames within a specific directory:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc os.OpenInRoot(string, string) (*File, error)\\n\\nf, err := os.OpenInRoot(\\\"/some/root/directory\\\", untrustedFilename)\\n```\\n\\n## How It Works\\n\\n- **Disallows path escaping** via `..` components or symlinks that escape the root\\n- **Permits safe operations** like `root.Open(\\\"a/../b\\\")` (relative paths within bounds)\\n- **Platform-specific implementations:**\\n  - **Unix**: Uses `openat` family of syscalls with file descriptor tracking\\n  - **Windows**: Uses directory handles, prevents reserved names (`NUL`, `COM1`)\\n  - **WASI**: Leverages WASI preview 1 filesystem API\\n  - **Plan 9**: Lexical path sanitization (no symlinks)\\n  - **Node.js (GOOS=js)**: Limited TOCTOU protection\\n\\n## When to Use\\n\\nUse `os.Root` or `os.OpenInRoot` when:\\n- Opening files in a specific directory AND\\n- The operation must not access files outside that directory\\n\\n**Example - Archive Extractor:**\\n```go\\n// Instead of:\\nf, err := os.Open(filepath.Join(baseDirectory, filename))\\n\\n// Use:\\nf, err := os.OpenInRoot(baseDirectory, filename)\\n```\\n\\n**When NOT to use:** Command-line programs accepting user-specified file paths (filename is trusted and may access anywhere on filesystem).\\n\\n## Related Existing APIs\\n\\n- **Go 1.20**: [`filepath.IsLocal()`](/pkg/path/filepath#IsLocal) - validates if path is \\\"local\\\"\\n- **Go 1.23**: [`filepath.Localize()`](/pkg/path/filepath#Localize) - converts /-separated paths to local OS paths\"}]},\"uuid\":\"2455b006-6bdc-498a-ab0a-e63748371d26\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-16T13:23:58.349Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"bytes\":43601,\"code\":200,\"codeText\":\"OK\",\"result\":\"# Traversal-resistant File APIs in Go 1.24\\n\\n## Problem Solved\\nPath traversal vulnerabilities occur when attackers trick programs into opening unintended files by:\\n- Using relative directory components (`../../../etc/passwd`)\\n- Exploiting Windows reserved names (`CONOUT$`)\\n- Creating symbolic links to escape the intended directory\\n- Executing time-of-check/time-of-use (TOCTOU) races\\n\\n## New APIs (Go 1.24)\\n\\n### `os.Root` Type\\nRepresents a directory in the local filesystem, providing traversal-resistant file operations.\\n\\n**Constructor:**\\n```go\\nfunc os.OpenRoot(string) (*Root, error)\\n\\nroot, err := os.OpenRoot(\\\"/some/root/directory\\\")\\nif err != nil {\\n  return err\\n}\\ndefer root.Close()\\n```\\n\\n**Methods:**\\n```go\\nfunc (*Root) Create(string) (*File, error)\\nfunc (*Root) Lstat(string) (fs.FileInfo, error)\\nfunc (*Root) Mkdir(string, fs.FileMode) error\\nfunc (*Root) Open(string) (*File, error)\\nfunc (*Root) OpenFile(string, int, fs.FileMode) (*File, error)\\nfunc (*Root) OpenRoot(string) (*Root, error)\\nfunc (*Root) Remove(string) error\\nfunc (*Root) Stat(string) (fs.FileInfo, error)\\n```\\n\\n**Usage:**\\n```go\\nf, err := root.Open(\\\"path/to/file\\\")\\n```\\n\\n### `os.OpenInRoot` Function\\nConvenience function for opening untrusted filenames within a specific directory:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc os.OpenInRoot(string, string) (*File, error)\\n\\nf, err := os.OpenInRoot(\\\"/some/root/directory\\\", untrusted