_012Ndw63ANh7VWiAMTKBG6w4\",\"uuid\":\"124cb38f-4adc-4071-9cc1-364cffa002a7\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-16T14:04:59.328Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"c42b5c72-c49c-4b74-8715-bfd38547eb46\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/os-root-traversal-resistant\",\"slug\":\"radiant-wondering-turtle\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"124cb38f-4adc-4071-9cc1-364cffa002a7\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-16T14:05:26.938Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01Uk6TueRs4Bx7AUoevVP7C8\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_017vYhaerwUUWwjTYMVt1evH\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/docs/requirements/os-root-traversal-resistance/SUMMARY.md\",\"content\":\"# Summary: os.Root Traversal-Resistant File APIs\\n\\n## What Was Implemented\\n\\nIntroduced `os.Root` (Go 1.24+) traversal-resistant file I/O across four locations in the CLI, providing kernel-enforced path containment that prevents symlink attacks, TOCTOU races, and path traversal escapes.\\n\\n### Shared Package: `cmd/entire/cli/osroot/`\\n\\nCreated a new shared `osroot` package with four helpers:\\n- `ReadFile(root, name)` - traversal-resistant file read\\n- `WriteFile(root, name, data, perm)` - traversal-resistant file write\\n- `Remove(root, name)` - traversal-resistant file remove (no-op on missing)\\n- `Stat(root, name)` - traversal-resistant stat\\n\\nErrors are returned unwrapped to preserve `os.IsNotExist()` compatibility, which is critical for the nil-nil \\\"not found\\\" return pattern used throughout the codebase.\\n\\n### Tier 1: Session State Store (`session/state.go`)\\n- `Load()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `.git/entire-sessions/`, reads session JSON via `osroot.ReadFile`\\n- `Save()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `.git/entire-sessions/`, writes temp file via `osroot.WriteFile`, then renames (rename stays as `os.Rename` since not available on `os.Root`)\\n- `Clear()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `.git/entire-sessions/`, removes files via `osroot.Remove`\\n\\n### Tier 1: Pre-Prompt/Task State Files (`state.go`)\\n- `CapturePrePromptState()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `.entire/tmp/`, writes via `osroot.WriteFile`\\n- `LoadPrePromptState()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `.entire/tmp/`, reads via `osroot.ReadFile`\\n- `CleanupPrePromptState()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `.entire/tmp/`, removes via `osroot.Remove`\\n- Same pattern applied to `CapturePreTaskState()`, `LoadPreTaskState()`, `CleanupPreTaskState()`\\n\\n### Tier 2: Rewind File Restoration (`strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go`)\\n- `Rewind()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to repo root, uses `osroot.WriteFile` for restoring files and `osroot.Remove` for deleting untracked files\\n- `MkdirAll` stays as `os.MkdirAll` (not available on `os.Root`)\\n\\n### Tier 2: Task Metadata (`metadata.go` and `strategy/strategy.go`)\\n- `WriteTaskCheckpoint()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `taskMetadataDir`, writes via `osroot.WriteFile`\\n- `ReadTaskCheckpoint()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `taskMetadataDir`, reads via `osroot.ReadFile` (both `cli` and `strategy` package versions)\\n- `WriteTaskPrompt()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `taskMetadataDir`, writes via `osroot.WriteFile`\\n\\n## Tests Added\\n\\n### New test file: `cmd/entire/cli/osroot/osroot_test.go`\\n- `TestReadFile`, `TestReadFile_NotFound`, `TestReadFile_TraversalBlocked`\\n- `TestWriteFile`, `TestWriteFile_Overwrite`, `TestWriteFile_TraversalBlocked`\\n- `TestRemove`, `TestRemove_NotFound`, `TestRemove_TraversalBlocked`\\n- `TestStat`, `TestStat_NotFound`\\n- `TestSymlinkTraversal_ReadBlocked`, `TestSymlinkTraversal_WriteBlocked`\\n\\n### New test file: `cmd/entire/cli/osroot_test.go`\\n- `TestRootReadFile_Delegated`, `TestRootWriteFile_Delegated`, `TestRootRemove_Delegated`\\n\\n### Added to `cmd/entire/cli/session/state_test.go`\\n- `TestStateStore_Load_TraversalResistant` - validates path traversal is rejected\\n- `TestStateStore_Save_UsesOsRoot` - validates os.Root write path works\\n\\n## Design Decisions\\n\\n1. **Separate `osroot` package**: Avoids import cycles. Both `cli` and `session` packages need these helpers, but `session` cannot import `cli`. The `osroot` package has zero internal dependencies.\\n\\n2. **Unwrapped errors**: The `osroot` package returns errors from `os.Root` methods unwrapped. This preserves `os.IsNotExist()` compatibility, which is critical for the nil-nil \\\"not found\\\" return pattern used by `StateStore.Load()`, `LoadPrePromptState()`, etc.\\n\\n3. **MkdirAll/Rename stay as-is**: These operations are not available on `os.Root`. Directory creation uses `os.MkdirAll` with validated paths, and atomic renames use `os.Rename`. Both still benefit from the lexical validation already in place.\\n\\n4. **Thin wrappers in `cli` package**: `rootReadFile`, `rootWriteFile`, `rootRemove` in `osroot.go` delegate to the shared package, keeping the `cli` package API consistent while avoiding code duplication.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n- `mise run fmt` - clean\\n- `mise run lint` - 0 issues\\n- `mise run test:ci` - all tests pass (unit + integration + 47 E2E canary tests)\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":160,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":123136,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":160,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CZ6tMBFxXVu4BbeysQEm9\",\"uuid\":\"a61e2eab-4069-46c3-8368-5d0d72f83845\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a160521c0d4f524fc\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01Q7u3JHNk92fK6F52o8sQ13\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_012Ndw63ANh7VWiAMTKBG6w4\",\"uuid\":\"ac6e1a72-96b3-43c9-b8fc-6