rsal-resistant\",\"slug\":\"radiant-wondering-turtle\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"e62da2da-e090-4c4a-8cea-d0712de7a9f5\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01GGwdT8zNacfkNVK5KCCMf9\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Summary: os.Root Traversal-Resistant File APIs\\n     2→\\n     3→## What Was Implemented\\n     4→\\n     5→Introduced `os.Root` (Go 1.24+) traversal-resistant file I/O across four locations in the CLI, providing kernel-enforced path containment that prevents symlink attacks, TOCTOU races, and path traversal escapes.\\n     6→\\n     7→### Shared Package: `cmd/entire/cli/osroot/`\\n     8→\\n     9→Created a new shared `osroot` package with four helpers:\\n    10→- `ReadFile(root, name)` - traversal-resistant file read\\n    11→- `WriteFile(root, name, data, perm)` - traversal-resistant file write\\n    12→- `Remove(root, name)` - traversal-resistant file remove (no-op on missing)\\n    13→- `Stat(root, name)` - traversal-resistant stat\\n    14→\\n    15→Errors are returned unwrapped to preserve `os.IsNotExist()` compatibility, which is critical for the nil-nil \\\"not found\\\" return pattern used throughout the codebase.\\n    16→\\n    17→### Tier 1: Session State Store (`session/state.go`)\\n    18→- `Load()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `.git/entire-sessions/`, reads session JSON via `osroot.ReadFile`\\n    19→- `Save()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `.git/entire-sessions/`, writes temp file via `osroot.WriteFile`, then renames (rename stays as `os.Rename` since not available on `os.Root`)\\n    20→- `Clear()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `.git/entire-sessions/`, removes files via `osroot.Remove`\\n    21→\\n    22→### Tier 1: Pre-Prompt/Task State Files (`state.go`)\\n    23→- `CapturePrePromptState()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `.entire/tmp/`, writes via `osroot.WriteFile`\\n    24→- `LoadPrePromptState()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `.entire/tmp/`, reads via `osroot.ReadFile`\\n    25→- `CleanupPrePromptState()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `.entire/tmp/`, removes via `osroot.Remove`\\n    26→- Same pattern applied to `CapturePreTaskState()`, `LoadPreTaskState()`, `CleanupPreTaskState()`\\n    27→\\n    28→### Tier 2: Rewind File Restoration (`strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go`)\\n    29→- `Rewind()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to repo root, uses `osroot.WriteFile` for restoring files and `osroot.Remove` for deleting untracked files\\n    30→- `MkdirAll` stays as `os.MkdirAll` (not available on `os.Root`)\\n    31→\\n    32→### Tier 2: Task Metadata (`metadata.go` and `strategy/strategy.go`)\\n    33→- `WriteTaskCheckpoint()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `taskMetadataDir`, writes via `osroot.WriteFile`\\n    34→- `ReadTaskCheckpoint()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `taskMetadataDir`, reads via `osroot.ReadFile` (both `cli` and `strategy` package versions)\\n    35→- `WriteTaskPrompt()`: Opens `os.Root` scoped to `taskMetadataDir`, writes via `osroot.WriteFile`\\n    36→\\n    37→## Tests Added\\n    38→\\n    39→### New test file: `cmd/entire/cli/osroot/osroot_test.go`\\n    40→- `TestReadFile`, `TestReadFile_NotFound`, `TestReadFile_TraversalBlocked`\\n    41→- `TestWriteFile`, `TestWriteFile_Overwrite`, `TestWriteFile_TraversalBlocked`\\n    42→- `TestRemove`, `TestRemove_NotFound`, `TestRemove_TraversalBlocked`\\n    43→- `TestStat`, `TestStat_NotFound`\\n    44→- `TestSymlinkTraversal_ReadBlocked`, `TestSymlinkTraversal_WriteBlocked`\\n    45→\\n    46→### New test file: `cmd/entire/cli/osroot_test.go`\\n    47→- `TestRootReadFile_Delegated`, `TestRootWriteFile_Delegated`, `TestRootRemove_Delegated`\\n    48→\\n    49→### Added to `cmd/entire/cli/session/state_test.go`\\n    50→- `TestStateStore_Load_TraversalResistant` - validates path traversal is rejected\\n    51→- `TestStateStore_Save_UsesOsRoot` - validates os.Root write path works\\n    52→\\n    53→## Design Decisions\\n    54→\\n    55→1. **Separate `osroot` package**: Avoids import cycles. Both `cli` and `session` packages need these helpers, but `session` cannot import `cli`. The `osroot` package has zero internal dependencies.\\n    56→\\n    57→2. **Unwrapped errors**: The `osroot` package returns errors from `os.Root` methods unwrapped. This preserves `os.IsNotExist()` compatibility, which is critical for the nil-nil \\\"not found\\\" return pattern used by `StateStore.Load()`, `LoadPrePromptState()`, etc.\\n    58→\\n    59→3. **MkdirAll/Rename stay as-is**: These operations are not available on `os.Root`. Directory creation uses `os.MkdirAll` with validated paths, and atomic renames use `os.Rename`. Both still benefit from the lexical validation already in place.\\n    60→\\n    61→4. **Thin wrappers in `cli` package**: `rootReadFile`, `rootWriteFile`, `rootRemove` in `osroot.go` delegate to the shared package, keeping the `cli` package API consistent while avoiding code duplication.\\n    62→\\n    63→## Verification\\n    64→\\n    65→- `mise run fmt` - clean\\n    66→- `mise run lint` - 0 issues\\n    67→- `mise run test:ci` - all tests pass (unit + integration + 47 E2E canary tests)\\n    68→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"b6792405-da9a-4a45-a27d-4cec3926c963\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-16T14:17:50.790Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"af9b8156ee35593dd\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_015faihdnYxsRor5fBZjZ5Q1\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01PKbdUR9HbmVxyCq7FeYJWp\",\"uuid\":\"6410a3dd-6e86-46f6-a0c6-a0eccd0ca656\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-16T14:17:50.814Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"c42b5c72-c49c-4b74-8715-bfd38547eb46\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/os-root-traversal-resistant\",\"slug\":\"radiant-wondering-turtle\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"6410a3dd-6e86-46f6-a0c6-a0eccd0ca656\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-16T14:18:07.515Z\"