tif err := validation.ValidateSessionID(sessionID); err != nil {\\n   371→\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"invalid session ID: %w\\\", err)\\n   372→\\t}\\n   373→\\n   374→\\t// Remove all files for this session (state .json, .model hint, any future hint files).\\n   375→\\t// filepath.Glob finds matches; os.Root ensures traversal-resistant removal.\\n   376→\\tmatches, _ := filepath.Glob(filepath.Join(s.stateDir, sessionID+\\\".*\\\")) //nolint:errcheck // pattern is always valid\\n   377→\\tif len(matches) > 0 {\\n   378→\\t\\troot, rootErr := os.OpenRoot(s.stateDir)\\n   379→\\t\\tif rootErr != nil {\\n   380→\\t\\t\\t// Fall back to direct removal if root can't be opened\\n   381→\\t\\t\\tfor _, f := range matches {\\n   382→\\t\\t\\t\\t_ = os.Remove(f)\\n   383→\\t\\t\\t}\\n   384→\\t\\t\\treturn nil\\n   385→\\t\\t}\\n   386→\\t\\tdefer root.Close()\\n   387→\\t\\tfor _, f := range matches {\\n   388→\\t\\t\\t_ = osroot.Remove(root, filepath.Base(f)) //nolint:errcheck // best-effort cleanup\\n   389→\\t\\t}\\n   390→\\t}\\n   391→\\n   392→\\treturn nil\\n   393→}\\n   394→\\n   395→// RemoveAll removes the entire session state directory.\\n   396→// This is used during uninstall to completely remove all session state.\\n   397→func (s *StateStore) RemoveAll() error {\\n   398→\\tif err := os.RemoveAll(s.stateDir); err != nil {\\n   399→\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to remove session state directory: %w\\\", err)\"}]},\"uuid\":\"97b891c1-ef2d-41f0-8505-c420243e9094\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-16T14:32:46.974Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"af9dd70cd0b8f0842\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01M7YoYWnmRXX1az5GWqUrDU\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01STDYSpnnrQeawh99vFo4TN\",\"uuid\":\"b907157d-7de8-49a0-9cd6-f0f41c2f5696\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-16T14:32:46.982Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"c42b5c72-c49c-4b74-8715-bfd38547eb46\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/os-root-traversal-resistant\",\"slug\":\"radiant-wondering-turtle\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"b907157d-7de8-49a0-9cd6-f0f41c2f5696\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-16T14:33:21.926Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01QnGpwnmstmCXrmnecKsCHp\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01NvD3yYYPESXj1zj391TLN1\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/docs/requirements/os-root-traversal-resistance/review-02.md\",\"content\":\"# Review 02\\n\\n> Status: pending-dev\\n> Date: 2026-03-16\\n> Reviewer: Code Review Agent\\n> Verdict: APPROVE\\n\\n## Previous Review Status (review-01)\\n\\n- [x] Dead code (`cmd/entire/cli/osroot.go` and `osroot_test.go` wrappers) - FIXED. Files removed entirely; the `osroot` package in its own directory is the sole implementation.\\n- [x] Missing input validation in `state.go` pre-prompt/pre-task functions - FIXED. `validation.ValidateSessionID()` added to `CapturePrePromptState`, `LoadPrePromptState`, `CleanupPrePromptState`; `validation.ValidateToolUseID()` added to `CapturePreTaskState`, `LoadPreTaskState`, `CleanupPreTaskState`.\\n- [x] Misleading nolint comments (`//nolint:wrapcheck // error context in osroot.Remove`) - FIXED. Changed to `//nolint:wrapcheck // best-effort cleanup, caller adds context via wrapping function name`.\\n- [x] `openAllowedRoot` comment about resolving \\\"dst through symlinks\\\" - FIXED. Comment now clarifies: \\\"Only the parent directory is resolved; the final component may not exist yet.\\\"\\n- [x] `prePromptStateFile` and `preTaskStateFile` nearly dead code - FIXED. Moved to `state_test.go` as test-only helpers with clear comments.\\n\\n## New Findings\\n\\n### Critical (Must Fix)\\n\\nNone.\\n\\n### Important (Should Fix)\\n\\n- **[cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go:377-384] `Clear` still falls back to `os.Remove` when `os.OpenRoot` fails.** This was flagged as a Suggestion in review-01, but it deserves a bit more scrutiny. After adding `ValidateSessionID` (which prevents traversal via the session ID itself), the fallback is less dangerous -- the `filepath.Glob` pattern uses a validated session ID, so the matched files will be legitimate. However, the silent fallback means that if `os.OpenRoot` fails for reasons other than \\\"directory doesn't exist\\\" (e.g., permissions), the code silently degrades to non-root-scoped removal without any logging. Consider at minimum adding a `logging.Warn()` call when falling back, so operators can diagnose unexpected `os.OpenRoot` failures. This is not blocking.\\n\\n### Suggestions (Consider)\\n\\n- **[cmd/entire/cli/utils.go:98-108] `openAllowedRoot` still duplicates `paths.IsSubpath` logic.** This was noted in review-01. The inline comment explains the rationale (avoiding a redundant `filepath.Rel` call). Acceptable as-is, but if `IsSubpath` gains edge-case fixes in the future, this copy would drift. A `paths.IsSubpathFromRel(rel string) bool` helper would centralize the check. Low priority.\\n\\n- **[cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go:339-362] Atomic write uses `os.Root` for the temp file but `os.Rename` with `stateFilePath` for the rename.** This is documented in the comment (\\\"Rename is not available on os.Root, so we keep using os.Rename\\\") and the paths are validated via `ValidateSessionID`, so the approach is sound. Just noting that this is a known limitation of `os.Root` and the fallback is properly guarded by input validation.\\n\\n- **[cmd/entire/cli/osroot/osroot.go:40-51] `WriteFile` does not call `f.Sync()` before close.** This was noted in review-01. For the session state atomic-write path this is mitigated by the rename pattern, but for other callers (metadata writes, rewind file restoration), a crash between write and close could produce partial files. Low risk in practice.\\n\\n### Praise\\n\\n- All five critical and importa